=begin
  CritTracker (crittracker.lic) - GemStone IV / Lich (Ruby)
 
  Created by "Kaelyr the Vaalorn Wolf" using Claude AI.
  (This script was entirely AI generated, I am not a programmer.  As with any script, review it prior to use.)
  (I have tested this for my personal use, there may be bugs or inaccuracies.)

  Monitors your melee critical hits (CRUSH, PUNCTURE, SLASH only), and identifies the
  hit location, critical rank, and effects from the in-game messaging, and:
    * Sends a live one-line summary to the FAMILIAR window, e.g.
        CRUSH HEAD: RANK 9 | FATAL | R3 WOUND | DMG: 56
        SLASH RIGHT LEG: RANK 9 | STUN 12 ROUND | KNOCKDOWN | AMPUTATION | R3 WOUND | DMG: 88
    * Tracks DAILY and LIFETIME stats in the MAIN window: per damage-type and
      per location (hits, hit %, average/high damage, rank breakdown), an overall
      RANK TOTALS summary, plus weapon-swing count and complete-miss percentage.

  COMMANDS (type at the game prompt, NO leading semicolon - they are intercepted):
        crit daily            show today's stats (main window)
        crit life             show lifetime stats (main window)
        crit familiar         toggle the live familiar-window output on/off
        crit debug            toggle debug echo of unmatched post-hit lines
        crit reset daily      reset today's stats
        crit reset life       reset lifetime stats
        crit reset all        reset both
        crit help             show command help
  (You can also use the ;send form, e.g.  ;send crit daily )

  DATA SOURCE: messaging/damage/status/wounds transcribed verbatim from gswiki:
        https://gswiki.play.net/Crush_critical_table     (rev 209174)
        https://gswiki.play.net/Puncture_critical_table  (rev 209175)
        https://gswiki.play.net/Slash_critical_table     (rev 111839)

  NOTES / LIMITATIONS (see chat for full explanation):
    * Detection works by matching the exact crit MESSAGE text, since the game
      stream never prints type/location/rank explicitly.
    * Some crit messages are identical for the LEFT and RIGHT version of a limb.
      Those are genuinely side-less in the game text, so they are recorded under
      the base location (e.g. ARM, HAND, LEG, EYE) rather than guessing a side.
    * Complete misses use the d100 endroll (<=100 = miss) from the AS vs DS line.
      DMG is always the weapon swing's "and hit for N" value, never a flare's.
    * The player's own hit is detected via the "...and hit for N points of
      damage!" line. Incoming hits ("hits you for...") and other players' hits
      ("hits the X for...") are filtered out. CS/spell/ranged messaging differs
      and is not the target of this melee tracker. Non-corporeal creatures use a
      separate, non-injuring message set and are intentionally NOT tracked.
    * Non-Corp and Flare crits are purposefully omitted.

=end

module CritTracker
  extend self
  no_kill_all

  require 'yaml'

  HOOK_ID = "crittracker-cmd"

  # ---- Critical tables ---------------------------------------------------
